Summary: This chunk lists the available trigonometric functions in Godot's shader language, including standard and hyperbolic functions, and their inverses.

Trigonometric functions

*   radians(vec_type degrees) (returns vec_type): Convert degrees to radians.
*   degrees(vec_type radians) (returns vec_type): Convert radians to degrees.
*   sin(vec_type x) (returns vec_type): Sine.
*   cos(vec_type x) (returns vec_type): Cosine.
*   tan(vec_type x) (returns vec_type): Tangent.
*   asin(vec_type x) (returns vec_type): Arc sine.
*   acos(vec_type x) (returns vec_type): Arc cosine.
*   atan(vec_type y_over_x) (returns vec_type): Arc tangent.
*   atan(vec_type y, vec_type x) (returns vec_type): Arc tangent.
*   sinh(vec_type x) (returns vec_type): Hyperbolic sine.
*   cosh(vec_type x) (returns vec_type): Hyperbolic cosine.
*   tanh(vec_type x) (returns vec_type): Hyperbolic tangent.
*   asinh(vec_type x) (returns vec_type): Arc hyperbolic sine.
*   acosh(vec_type x) (returns vec_type): Arc hyperbolic cosine.
*   atanh(vec_type x) (returns vec_type): Arc hyperbolic tangent.
