Path: godot/tutorials/shaders/shader_reference/shader_functions.rst
Summary: This chunk covers the shader functions `intBitsToFloat` and `uintBitsToFloat`, which convert integer bit encodings into floating-point values.

Method: vec_type intBitsToFloat(vec_int_type x)
This function operates component-wise. It converts a bit encoding to a floating-point value and is the opposite of `floatBitsToInt`. If the encoding of a NaN is passed in `x`, it will not signal and the resulting value will be undefined. If the encoding of a floating-point infinity is passed in parameter `x`, the resulting floating-point value is the corresponding (positive or negative) floating-point infinity.
`x`: The bit encoding to return as a floating-point value.
Returns: A floating-point value.

Method: vec_type uintBitsToFloat(vec_uint_type x)
This function operates component-wise. It converts a bit encoding to a floating-point value and is the opposite of `floatBitsToUint`. If the encoding of a NaN is passed in `x`, it will not signal and the resulting value will be undefined. If the encoding of a floating-point infinity is passed in parameter `x`, the resulting floating-point value is the corresponding (positive or negative) floating-point infinity.
`x`: The bit encoding to return as a floating-point value.
Returns: A floating-point value.
---CHUNK---
